6 CONCLUSION
In this work we demonstrate that models based on self-attention can operate effectively on modalities other than text and through local self-attention scale to significantly larger structures than sentences. We further hope to have provided additional evidence that even in the light of generative adversarial networks, autoregressive generation of images is very much a promising area for further research as is using network architectures such as the Image Transformer in GANs. In future work we would like to explore a broader variety of conditioning information including free-form text, as previously proposed (Mansimov et al., 2015), and tasks combining modalities such as language-driven editing of images. Fundamentally we aim to move beyond still images to video (Kalchbrenner et al., 2016) and towards applications of such models in more model-based reinforcement learning approaches.
